    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "CT head\nto rule out other etiologies\nMRI\noften shows symmetrical cerebral edema, showing as hyperintensities on T2-weighted image in the posterior circulation, most commonly in the parietal-occipital areas\n[5]\nHowever, any brain region can be involved, including the frontal and temporal lobes\nFocus on\naltered mental status workup\n, with PRES as diagnosis of exclusion\nConsider\nlumbar puncture\nif there is a concern for\nmeningitis\nor\nencephalitis\nMay require EEG for detection of status epilepticus",
